    "description": "<p>This spell paralyzes normal or giant-sized animals within a range of 180'. The spell does not affect creatures with greater than animal intelligence (2) or fantastic creatures.</p>\n                      <p><strong>Effect:</strong> Each animal makes a saving throw vs. spells to resist paralysis for the spell’s duration. The druid can affect 1 Hit Die of animals per caster level, ignoring any “pluses” to Hit Dice. For example, a 20th-level druid could hold 10 giant toads (2 + 2 HD each).</p>\n                      <p>This spell can also affect summoned, conjured, or controlled animals.</p>",
